-- | Settings related to the Amazon Chime account. This includes settings
--   that start or stop remote control of shared screens, or start or stop
--   the dial-out option in the Amazon Chime web application. For more
--   information about these settings, see <a>Use the Policies Page</a> in

--   without the Amazon Chime App</a>.

--   meetings.

module Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Attendee

-- | An Amazon Chime SDK meeting attendee. Includes a unique
--   <tt>AttendeeId</tt> and <tt>JoinToken</tt> . The <tt>JoinToken</tt>
--   allows a client to authenticate and join as the specified attendee.
--   The <tt>JoinToken</tt> expires when the meeting ends or when
--   DeleteAttendee is called. After that, the attendee is unable to join
--   the meeting.
--   
--   We recommend securely transferring each <tt>JoinToken</tt> from your
--   server application to the client so that no other client has access to
--   the token except for the one authorized to represent the attendee.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAttendee</a> smart constructor.
data Attendee
Attendee' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Attendee

-- | The Amazon Chime SDK attendee ID.
[$sel:attendeeId:Attendee'] :: Attendee -> Maybe Text

-- | The join token used by the Amazon Chime SDK attendee.
[$sel:joinToken:Attendee'] :: Attendee -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The Amazon Chime SDK external user ID. An idempotency token. Links the
--   attendee to an identity managed by a builder application.
[$sel:externalUserId:Attendee'] :: Attendee -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | Create a value of <a>Attendee</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:attendeeId:Attendee'</a>, <a>attendee_attendeeId</a> - The
--   Amazon Chime SDK attendee ID.
--   
--   <a>$sel:joinToken:Attendee'</a>, <a>attendee_joinToken</a> - The join
--   token used by the Amazon Chime SDK attendee.
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalUserId:Attendee'</a>, <a>attendee_externalUserId</a> -
--   The Amazon Chime SDK external user ID. An idempotency token. Links the
--   attendee to an identity managed by a builder application.
newAttendee :: Attendee

-- | The Amazon Chime SDK attendee ID.
attendee_attendeeId :: Lens' Attendee (Maybe Text)

-- | The join token used by the Amazon Chime SDK attendee.
attendee_joinToken :: Lens' Attendee (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon Chime SDK external user ID. An idempotency token. Links the
--   attendee to an identity managed by a builder application.
attendee_externalUserId :: Lens' Attendee (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Attendee.Attendee
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Attendee.Attendee
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Attendee.Attendee
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Attendee.Attendee
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Attendee.Attendee
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Attendee.Attendee

module Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Bot

-- | A resource that allows Enterprise account administrators to configure
--   an interface to receive events from Amazon Chime.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newBot</a> smart constructor.
data Bot
Bot' :: Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe BotType -> Bot

-- | The security token used to authenticate Amazon Chime with the outgoing
--   event endpoint.
[$sel:securityToken:Bot'] :: Bot -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | When true, the bot is stopped from running in your account.
[$sel:disabled:Bot'] :: Bot -> Maybe Bool

-- | The updated bot timestamp, in ISO 8601 format.
[$sel:updatedTimestamp:Bot'] :: Bot -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The unique ID for the bot user.
[$sel:userId:Bot'] :: Bot -> Maybe Text

-- | The bot ID.
[$sel:botId:Bot'] :: Bot -> Maybe Text

-- | The bot display name.
[$sel:displayName:Bot'] :: Bot -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The bot email address.
[$sel:botEmail:Bot'] :: Bot -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The bot creation timestamp, in ISO 8601 format.
[$sel:createdTimestamp:Bot'] :: Bot -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The bot type.
[$sel:botType:Bot'] :: Bot -> Maybe BotType

-- | Create a value of <a>Bot</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:securityToken:Bot'</a>, <a>bot_securityToken</a> - The
--   security token used to authenticate Amazon Chime with the outgoing
--   event endpoint.
--   
--   <a>$sel:disabled:Bot'</a>, <a>bot_disabled</a> - When true, the bot is
--   stopped from running in your account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:updatedTimestamp:Bot'</a>, <a>bot_updatedTimestamp</a> - The
--   updated bot timestamp, in ISO 8601 format.
--   
--   <a>$sel:userId:Bot'</a>, <a>bot_userId</a> - The unique ID for the bot
--   user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:botId:Bot'</a>, <a>bot_botId</a> - The bot ID.
--   
--   <a>$sel:displayName:Bot'</a>, <a>bot_displayName</a> - The bot display
--   name.
--   
--   <a>$sel:botEmail:Bot'</a>, <a>bot_botEmail</a> - The bot email
--   address.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTimestamp:Bot'</a>, <a>bot_createdTimestamp</a> - The
--   bot creation timestamp, in ISO 8601 format.
--   
--   <a>$sel:botType:Bot'</a>, <a>bot_botType</a> - The bot type.
newBot :: Bot

-- | The security token used to authenticate Amazon Chime with the outgoing
--   event endpoint.
bot_securityToken :: Lens' Bot (Maybe Text)

-- | When true, the bot is stopped from running in your account.
bot_disabled :: Lens' Bot (Maybe Bool)

-- | The updated bot timestamp, in ISO 8601 format.
bot_updatedTimestamp :: Lens' Bot (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The unique ID for the bot user.
bot_userId :: Lens' Bot (Maybe Text)

-- | The bot ID.
bot_botId :: Lens' Bot (Maybe Text)

-- | The bot display name.
bot_displayName :: Lens' Bot (Maybe Text)

-- | The bot email address.
bot_botEmail :: Lens' Bot (Maybe Text)

-- | The bot creation timestamp, in ISO 8601 format.
bot_createdTimestamp :: Lens' Bot (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The bot type.
bot_botType :: Lens' Bot (Maybe BotType)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Bot.Bot
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Bot.Bot
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Bot.Bot
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Bot.Bot
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Bot.Bot
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Bot.Bot

-- | The mode of the channel.
[$sel:mode:ChannelSummary'] :: ChannelSummary -> Maybe ChannelMode

[$sel:channelArn:ChannelSummary'] :: ChannelSummary -> Maybe Text

[$sel:privacy:ChannelSummary'] :: ChannelSummary -> Maybe ChannelPrivacy

[$sel:lastMessageTimestamp:ChannelSummary'] :: ChannelSummary -> Maybe POSIX

--

module Network.AWS.Chime.Types.BatchChannelMemberships

--

data BatchChannelMemberships

-- | The users successfully added to the request.
[$sel:members:BatchChannelMemberships'] :: BatchChannelMemberships -> Maybe [Identity]

[$sel:channelArn:BatchChannelMemberships'] :: BatchChannelMemberships -> Maybe Text

-- | The membership types set for the channel users.
[$sel:type':BatchChannelMemberships'] :: BatchChannelMemberships -> Maybe ChannelMembershipType

-- | The identifier of the member who invited another member.
[$sel:invitedBy:BatchChannelMemberships'] :: BatchChannelMemberships -> Maybe Identity

-- | Create a value of <a>BatchChannelMemberships</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:members:BatchChannelMemberships'</a>,
--   <a>batchChannelMemberships_members</a> - The users successfully added
--   to the request.
--   
--   <a>$sel:channelArn:BatchChannelMemberships'</a>,
--   <a>batchChannelMemberships_channelArn</a> - The ARN of the channel to
--   which you're adding users.
--   
--   <a>$sel:type':BatchChannelMemberships'</a>,
--   <a>batchChannelMemberships_type</a> - The membership types set for the
--   channel users.
--   
--   <a>$sel:invitedBy:BatchChannelMemberships'</a>,
--   <a>batchChannelMemberships_invitedBy</a> - The identifier of the
--   member who invited another member.
newBatchChannelMemberships :: BatchChannelMemberships

-- | The users successfully added to the request.
batchChannelMemberships_members :: Lens' BatchChannelMemberships (Maybe [Identity])

-- | The ARN of the channel to which you're adding users.
batchChannelMemberships_channelArn :: Lens' BatchChannelMemberships (Maybe Text)

-- | The membership types set for the channel users.
batchChannelMemberships_type :: Lens' BatchChannelMemberships (Maybe ChannelMembershipType)

-- | The identifier of the member who invited another member.
batchChannelMemberships_invitedBy :: Lens' BatchChannelMemberships (Maybe Identity)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.Chime.Types.BatchChannelMemberships.BatchChannelMemberships
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Chime.Types.BatchChannelMemberships.BatchChannelMemberships
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.Chime.Types.BatchChannelMemberships.BatchChannelMemberships
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.Chime.Types.BatchChannelMemberships.BatchChannelMemberships

module Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Meeting

-- | A meeting created using the Amazon Chime SDK.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newMeeting</a> smart constructor.
data Meeting
Meeting' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe MediaPlacement -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe Text -> Meeting

-- | The Region in which you create the meeting. Available values:
--   <tt>af-south-1</tt>, <tt>ap-northeast-1</tt>, <tt>ap-northeast-2</tt>,
--   <tt>ap-south-1</tt>, <tt>ap-southeast-1</tt>, <tt>ap-southeast-2</tt>,
--   <tt>ca-central-1</tt>, <tt>eu-central-1</tt>, <tt>eu-north-1</tt>,
--   <tt>eu-south-1</tt>, <tt>eu-west-1</tt>, <tt>eu-west-2</tt>,
--   <tt>eu-west-3</tt>, <tt>sa-east-1</tt>, <tt>us-east-1</tt>,
--   <tt>us-east-2</tt>, <tt>us-west-1</tt>, <tt>us-west-2</tt>.
[$sel:mediaRegion:Meeting'] :: Meeting -> Maybe Text

-- | The media placement for the meeting.
[$sel:mediaPlacement:Meeting'] :: Meeting -> Maybe MediaPlacement

-- | The external meeting ID.
[$sel:externalMeetingId:Meeting'] :: Meeting -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The Amazon Chime SDK meeting ID.

module Network.AWS.Chime.Types.OriginationRoute

-- | Origination routes define call distribution properties for your SIP
--   hosts to receive inbound calls using your Amazon Chime Voice
--   Connector. Limit: Ten origination routes for each Amazon Chime Voice
--   Connector.
--   
--   The parameters listed below are not required, but you must use at
--   least one.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOriginationRoute</a> smart constructor.
data OriginationRoute
OriginationRoute' :: Maybe Natural -> Maybe Natural -> Maybe OriginationRouteProtocol -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Natural -> OriginationRoute

-- | The priority associated with the host, with 1 being the highest
--   priority. Higher priority hosts are attempted first.
[$sel:priority:OriginationRoute'] :: OriginationRoute -> Maybe Natural

-- | The weight associated with the host. If hosts are equal in priority,
--   calls are redistributed among them based on their relative weight.
[$sel:weight:OriginationRoute'] :: OriginationRoute -> Maybe Natural

-- | The protocol to use for the origination route. Encryption-enabled
--   Amazon Chime Voice Connectors use TCP protocol by default.
[$sel:protocol:OriginationRoute'] :: OriginationRoute -> Maybe OriginationRouteProtocol

-- | The FQDN or IP address to contact for origination traffic.
[$sel:host:OriginationRoute'] :: OriginationRoute -> Maybe Text

-- | The designated origination route port. Defaults to 5060.
[$sel:port:OriginationRoute'] :: OriginationRoute -> Maybe Natural

-- | Create a value of <a>OriginationRoute</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:priority:OriginationRoute'</a>,
--   <a>originationRoute_priority</a> - The priority associated with the
--   host, with 1 being the highest priority. Higher priority hosts are
--   attempted first.
--   
--   <a>$sel:weight:OriginationRoute'</a>, <a>originationRoute_weight</a> -
--   The weight associated with the host. If hosts are equal in priority,
--   calls are redistributed among them based on their relative weight.
--   
--   <a>$sel:protocol:OriginationRoute'</a>,
--   <a>originationRoute_protocol</a> - The protocol to use for the
--   origination route. Encryption-enabled Amazon Chime Voice Connectors
--   use TCP protocol by default.
--   
--   <a>$sel:host:OriginationRoute'</a>, <a>originationRoute_host</a> - The
--   FQDN or IP address to contact for origination traffic.
--   
--   <a>$sel:port:OriginationRoute'</a>, <a>originationRoute_port</a> - The
--   designated origination route port. Defaults to 5060.
newOriginationRoute :: OriginationRoute

-- | The priority associated with the host, with 1 being the highest
--   priority. Higher priority hosts are attempted first.
originationRoute_priority :: Lens' OriginationRoute (Maybe Natural)

-- | The weight associated with the host. If hosts are equal in priority,
--   calls are redistributed among them based on their relative weight.
originationRoute_weight :: Lens' OriginationRoute (Maybe Natural)

-- | The protocol to use for the origination route. Encryption-enabled
--   Amazon Chime Voice Connectors use TCP protocol by default.
originationRoute_protocol :: Lens' OriginationRoute (Maybe OriginationRouteProtocol)

-- | The FQDN or IP address to contact for origination traffic.
originationRoute_host :: Lens' OriginationRoute (Maybe Text)

-- | The designated origination route port. Defaults to 5060.
originationRoute_port :: Lens' OriginationRoute (Maybe Natural)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.Chime.Types.OriginationRoute.OriginationRoute
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Chime.Types.OriginationRoute.OriginationRoute
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.Chime.Types.OriginationRoute.OriginationRoute
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.Chime.Types.OriginationRoute.OriginationRoute
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.Chime.Types.OriginationRoute.OriginationRoute
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.Chime.Types.OriginationRoute.OriginationRoute
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.Chime.Types.OriginationRoute.OriginationRoute
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.Chime.Types.OriginationRoute.OriginationRoute


module Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Origination

-- | Origination settings enable your SIP hosts to receive inbound calls
--   using your Amazon Chime Voice Connector.
--   
--   The parameters listed below are not required, but you must use at
--   least one.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOrigination</a> smart constructor.
data Origination
Origination' :: Maybe [OriginationRoute] -> Maybe Bool -> Origination

-- | The call distribution properties defined for your SIP hosts. Valid
--   range: Minimum value of 1. Maximum value of 20. This parameter is not
--   required, but you must specify this parameter or <tt>Disabled</tt>.
[$sel:routes:Origination'] :: Origination -> Maybe [OriginationRoute]

-- | When origination settings are disabled, inbound calls are not enabled
--   for your Amazon Chime Voice Connector. This parameter is not required,
--   but you must specify this parameter or <tt>Routes</tt>.
[$sel:disabled:Origination'] :: Origination -> Maybe Bool

-- | Create a value of <a>Origination</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:routes:Origination'</a>, <a>origination_routes</a> - The call
--   distribution properties defined for your SIP hosts. Valid range:
--   Minimum value of 1. Maximum value of 20. This parameter is not
--   required, but you must specify this parameter or <tt>Disabled</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:disabled:Origination'</a>, <a>origination_disabled</a> - When
--   origination settings are disabled, inbound calls are not enabled for
--   your Amazon Chime Voice Connector. This parameter is not required, but
--   you must specify this parameter or <tt>Routes</tt>.
newOrigination :: Origination

-- | The call distribution properties defined for your SIP hosts. Valid
--   range: Minimum value of 1. Maximum value of 20. This parameter is not
--   required, but you must specify this parameter or <tt>Disabled</tt>.
origination_routes :: Lens' Origination (Maybe [OriginationRoute])

-- | When origination settings are disabled, inbound calls are not enabled
--   for your Amazon Chime Voice Connector. This parameter is not required,
--   but you must specify this parameter or <tt>Routes</tt>.
origination_disabled :: Lens' Origination (Maybe Bool)

module Network.AWS.Chime.Types.PhoneNumberOrder

-- | The details of a phone number order created for Amazon Chime.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newPhoneNumberOrder</a> smart constructor.
data PhoneNumberOrder
PhoneNumberOrder' :: Maybe PhoneNumberOrderStatus -> Maybe [OrderedPhoneNumber] -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe PhoneNumberProductType -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> PhoneNumberOrder

-- | The status of the phone number order.
[$sel:status:PhoneNumberOrder'] :: PhoneNumberOrder -> Maybe PhoneNumberOrderStatus

-- | The ordered phone number details, such as the phone number in E.164
--   format and the phone number status.
[$sel:orderedPhoneNumbers:PhoneNumberOrder'] :: PhoneNumberOrder -> Maybe [OrderedPhoneNumber]

-- | The updated phone number order time stamp, in ISO 8601 format.
[$sel:updatedTimestamp:PhoneNumberOrder'] :: PhoneNumberOrder -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The phone number order product type.
[$sel:productType:PhoneNumberOrder'] :: PhoneNumberOrder -> Maybe PhoneNumberProductType

-- | The phone number order ID.
[$sel:phoneNumberOrderId:PhoneNumberOrder'] :: PhoneNumberOrder -> Maybe Text

-- | The phone number order creation time stamp, in ISO 8601 format.
[$sel:createdTimestamp:PhoneNumberOrder'] :: PhoneNumberOrder -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Create a value of <a>PhoneNumberOrder</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:PhoneNumberOrder'</a>, <a>phoneNumberOrder_status</a> -
--   The status of the phone number order.
--   
--   <a>$sel:orderedPhoneNumbers:PhoneNumberOrder'</a>,
--   <a>phoneNumberOrder_orderedPhoneNumbers</a> - The ordered phone number
--   details, such as the phone number in E.164 format and the phone number
--   status.
--   
--   <a>$sel:updatedTimestamp:PhoneNumberOrder'</a>,
--   <a>phoneNumberOrder_updatedTimestamp</a> - The updated phone number
--   order time stamp, in ISO 8601 format.
--   
--   <a>$sel:productType:PhoneNumberOrder'</a>,
--   <a>phoneNumberOrder_productType</a> - The phone number order product
--   type.
--   
--   <a>$sel:phoneNumberOrderId:PhoneNumberOrder'</a>,
--   <a>phoneNumberOrder_phoneNumberOrderId</a> - The phone number order
--   ID.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTimestamp:PhoneNumberOrder'</a>,
--   <a>phoneNumberOrder_createdTimestamp</a> - The phone number order
--   creation time stamp, in ISO 8601 format.
newPhoneNumberOrder :: PhoneNumberOrder

-- | The phone number order creation time stamp, in ISO 8601 format.

--   Chime Voice Connector.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newPhoneNumber</a> smart constructor.
data PhoneNumber
PhoneNumber' :: Maybe PhoneNumberStatus -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe PhoneNumberProductType -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe [PhoneNumberAssociation] -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe PhoneNumberType -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe PhoneNumberCapabilities -> Maybe CallingNameStatus -> PhoneNumber

-- | The phone number status.

-- | The phone number, in E.164 format.
[$sel:e164PhoneNumber:PhoneNumber'] :: PhoneNumber -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The phone number associations.
[$sel:associations:PhoneNumber'] :: PhoneNumber -> Maybe [PhoneNumberAssociation]

-- | The outbound calling name associated with the phone number.
[$sel:callingName:PhoneNumber'] :: PhoneNumber -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The phone number type.
[$sel:type':PhoneNumber'] :: PhoneNumber -> Maybe PhoneNumberType

-- | The phone number creation timestamp, in ISO 8601 format.
[$sel:createdTimestamp:PhoneNumber'] :: PhoneNumber -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The phone number capabilities.
[$sel:capabilities:PhoneNumber'] :: PhoneNumber -> Maybe PhoneNumberCapabilities

-- | The outbound calling name status.
[$sel:callingNameStatus:PhoneNumber'] :: PhoneNumber -> Maybe CallingNameStatus

-- | Create a value of <a>PhoneNumber</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--

--   number status.

--   <a>$sel:deletionTimestamp:PhoneNumber'</a>,

--   timestamp, in ISO 8601 format.

--   <a>$sel:phoneNumberId:PhoneNumber'</a>,

module Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Proxy

-- | The proxy configuration for an Amazon Chime Voice Connector.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newProxy</a> smart constructor.
data Proxy
Proxy' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe [Text] -> Proxy

-- | The default number of minutes allowed for proxy sessions.
[$sel:defaultSessionExpiryMinutes:Proxy'] :: Proxy -> Maybe Int

-- | When true, stops proxy sessions from being created on the specified
--   Amazon Chime Voice Connector.
[$sel:disabled:Proxy'] :: Proxy -> Maybe Bool

-- | The phone number to route calls to after a proxy session expires.
[$sel:fallBackPhoneNumber:Proxy'] :: Proxy -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The countries for proxy phone numbers to be selected from.
[$sel:phoneNumberCountries:Proxy'] :: Proxy -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Create a value of <a>Proxy</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:defaultSessionExpiryMinutes:Proxy'</a>,
--   <a>proxy_defaultSessionExpiryMinutes</a> - The default number of
--   minutes allowed for proxy sessions.
--   
--   <a>$sel:disabled:Proxy'</a>, <a>proxy_disabled</a> - When true, stops
--   proxy sessions from being created on the specified Amazon Chime Voice
--   Connector.
--   
--   <a>$sel:fallBackPhoneNumber:Proxy'</a>,
--   <a>proxy_fallBackPhoneNumber</a> - The phone number to route calls to
--   after a proxy session expires.
--   
--   <a>$sel:phoneNumberCountries:Proxy'</a>,
--   <a>proxy_phoneNumberCountries</a> - The countries for proxy phone
--   numbers to be selected from.
newProxy :: Proxy

-- | The default number of minutes allowed for proxy sessions.
proxy_defaultSessionExpiryMinutes :: Lens' Proxy (Maybe Int)

-- | When true, stops proxy sessions from being created on the specified
--   Amazon Chime Voice Connector.
proxy_disabled :: Lens' Proxy (Maybe Bool)

proxy_fallBackPhoneNumber :: Lens' Proxy (Maybe Text)

-- | The countries for proxy phone numbers to be selected from.

module Network.AWS.Chime.Types.ProxySession

-- | The proxy session for an Amazon Chime Voice Connector.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newProxySession</a> smart constructor.
data ProxySession
ProxySession' :: Maybe ProxySessionStatus -> Maybe NumberSelectionBehavior -> Maybe GeoMatchParams -> Maybe Natural -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe [Participant] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe GeoMatchLevel -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe [Capability] -> ProxySession

-- | The status of the proxy session.
[$sel:status:ProxySession'] :: ProxySession -> Maybe ProxySessionStatus

-- | The preference for proxy phone number reuse, or stickiness, between
--   the same participants across sessions.
[$sel:numberSelectionBehavior:ProxySession'] :: ProxySession -> Maybe NumberSelectionBehavior

-- | The country and area code for the proxy phone number.
[$sel:geoMatchParams:ProxySession'] :: ProxySession -> Maybe GeoMatchParams

-- | The number of minutes allowed for the proxy session.
[$sel:expiryMinutes:ProxySession'] :: ProxySession -> Maybe Natural

-- | The ended time stamp, in ISO 8601 format.
[$sel:endedTimestamp:ProxySession'] :: ProxySession -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The updated time stamp, in ISO 8601 format.
[$sel:updatedTimestamp:ProxySession'] :: ProxySession -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The proxy session participants.
[$sel:participants:ProxySession'] :: ProxySession -> Maybe [Participant]

-- | The name of the proxy session.
[$sel:name:ProxySession'] :: ProxySession -> Maybe Text

-- | The proxy session ID.
[$sel:proxySessionId:ProxySession'] :: ProxySession -> Maybe Text

-- | The preference for matching the country or area code of the proxy
--   phone number with that of the first participant.
[$sel:geoMatchLevel:ProxySession'] :: ProxySession -> Maybe GeoMatchLevel

-- | The Amazon Chime voice connector ID.
[$sel:voiceConnectorId:ProxySession'] :: ProxySession -> Maybe Text

-- | The created time stamp, in ISO 8601 format.
[$sel:createdTimestamp:ProxySession'] :: ProxySession -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The proxy session capabilities.
[$sel:capabilities:ProxySession'] :: ProxySession -> Maybe [Capability]

-- | Create a value of <a>ProxySession</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:ProxySession'</a>, <a>proxySession_status</a> - The
--   status of the proxy session.
--   
--   <a>$sel:numberSelectionBehavior:ProxySession'</a>,
--   <a>proxySession_numberSelectionBehavior</a> - The preference for proxy
--   phone number reuse, or stickiness, between the same participants
--   across sessions.
--   
--   <a>$sel:geoMatchParams:ProxySession'</a>,
--   <a>proxySession_geoMatchParams</a> - The country and area code for the
--   proxy phone number.
--   
--   <a>$sel:expiryMinutes:ProxySession'</a>,
--   <a>proxySession_expiryMinutes</a> - The number of minutes allowed for
--   the proxy session.
--   
--   <a>$sel:endedTimestamp:ProxySession'</a>,
--   <a>proxySession_endedTimestamp</a> - The ended time stamp, in ISO 8601
--   format.
--   
--   <a>$sel:updatedTimestamp:ProxySession'</a>,
--   <a>proxySession_updatedTimestamp</a> - The updated time stamp, in ISO
--   8601 format.
--   
--   <a>$sel:participants:ProxySession'</a>,
--   <a>proxySession_participants</a> - The proxy session participants.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:ProxySession'</a>, <a>proxySession_name</a> - The name of
--   the proxy session.
--   
--   <a>$sel:proxySessionId:ProxySession'</a>,
--   <a>proxySession_proxySessionId</a> - The proxy session ID.
--   
--   <a>$sel:geoMatchLevel:ProxySession'</a>,
--   <a>proxySession_geoMatchLevel</a> - The preference for matching the
--   country or area code of the proxy phone number with that of the first
--   participant.
--   
--   <a>$sel:voiceConnectorId:ProxySession'</a>,
--   <a>proxySession_voiceConnectorId</a> - The Amazon Chime voice
--   connector ID.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTimestamp:ProxySession'</a>,
--   <a>proxySession_createdTimestamp</a> - The created time stamp, in ISO
--   8601 format.
--   
--   <a>$sel:capabilities:ProxySession'</a>,

-- | The Amazon Chime account details. An AWS account can have multiple
--   Amazon Chime accounts.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAccount</a> smart constructor.
data Account
Account' :: Maybe [SigninDelegateGroup] -> Maybe AccountStatus -> Maybe License -> Maybe [License] -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe AccountType -> Text -> Text -> Text -> Account

--   account types, see <a>Managing Your Amazon Chime Accounts</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon Chime Administration Guide</i>.

-- | The AWS account ID.
[$sel:awsAccountId:Account'] :: Account -> Text

-- | The Amazon Chime account ID.
[$sel:accountId:Account'] :: Account -> Text

-- | The Amazon Chime account name.
[$sel:name:Account'] :: Account -> Text

--

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   status of the account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:defaultLicense:Account'</a>, <a>account_defaultLicense</a> -
--   The default license for the Amazon Chime account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:supportedLicenses:Account'</a>,

--   Name (ARN) of the Lambda function. The function must be created in the
--   same AWS Region as the SIP media application.
newSipMediaApplicationEndpoint :: SipMediaApplicationEndpoint

-- | Valid Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Lambda function. The function
--   must be created in the same AWS Region as the SIP media application.
sipMediaApplicationEndpoint_lambdaArn :: Lens' SipMediaApplicationEndpoint (Maybe Text)

module Network.AWS.Chime.Types.SipRule

-- | The SIP rule details, including name, triggers, and target
--   applications. An AWS account can have multiple SIP rules.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSipRule</a> smart constructor.
data SipRule
SipRule' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe (NonEmpty SipRuleTargetApplication) -> Maybe SipRuleTriggerType -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> SipRule

-- | Indicates whether the SIP rule is enabled or disabled. You must
--   disable a rule before you can delete it.
[$sel:disabled:SipRule'] :: SipRule -> Maybe Bool

-- | Target SIP media application and other details, such as priority and
--   AWS Region, to be specified in the SIP rule. Only one SIP rule per AWS
--   Region can be provided.
[$sel:targetApplications:SipRule'] :: SipRule -> Maybe (NonEmpty SipRuleTargetApplication)

-- | The type of trigger assigned to the SIP rule in <tt>TriggerValue</tt>,
--   currently <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt> or <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>.
[$sel:triggerType:SipRule'] :: SipRule -> Maybe SipRuleTriggerType

-- | The time at which the SIP rule was last updated, in ISO 8601 format.
[$sel:updatedTimestamp:SipRule'] :: SipRule -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The name of the SIP rule.
[$sel:name:SipRule'] :: SipRule -> Maybe Text

-- | If <tt>TriggerType</tt> is <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt>, then the value
--   can be the outbound host name of the Amazon Chime Voice Connector. If
--   <tt>TriggerType</tt> is <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>, then the value can be
--   a customer-owned phone number in E164 format. <tt>SipRule</tt> is
--   triggered when a SIP rule requests host name or <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>
--   matches in the incoming SIP request.
[$sel:triggerValue:SipRule'] :: SipRule -> Maybe Text

-- | The time at which the SIP rule was created, in ISO 8601 format.
[$sel:createdTimestamp:SipRule'] :: SipRule -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The SIP rule ID.
[$sel:sipRuleId:SipRule'] :: SipRule -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>SipRule</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:disabled:SipRule'</a>, <a>sipRule_disabled</a> - Indicates
--   whether the SIP rule is enabled or disabled. You must disable a rule
--   before you can delete it.
--   
--   <a>$sel:targetApplications:SipRule'</a>,
--   <a>sipRule_targetApplications</a> - Target SIP media application and
--   other details, such as priority and AWS Region, to be specified in the
--   SIP rule. Only one SIP rule per AWS Region can be provided.
--   
--   <a>$sel:triggerType:SipRule'</a>, <a>sipRule_triggerType</a> - The
--   type of trigger assigned to the SIP rule in <tt>TriggerValue</tt>,
--   currently <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt> or <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:updatedTimestamp:SipRule'</a>, <a>sipRule_updatedTimestamp</a>
--   - The time at which the SIP rule was last updated, in ISO 8601 format.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:SipRule'</a>, <a>sipRule_name</a> - The name of the SIP
--   rule.
--   
--   <a>$sel:triggerValue:SipRule'</a>, <a>sipRule_triggerValue</a> - If
--   <tt>TriggerType</tt> is <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt>, then the value
--   can be the outbound host name of the Amazon Chime Voice Connector. If
--   <tt>TriggerType</tt> is <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>, then the value can be
--   a customer-owned phone number in E164 format. <tt>SipRule</tt> is
--   triggered when a SIP rule requests host name or <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>
--   matches in the incoming SIP request.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTimestamp:SipRule'</a>, <a>sipRule_createdTimestamp</a>
--   - The time at which the SIP rule was created, in ISO 8601 format.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sipRuleId:SipRule'</a>, <a>sipRule_sipRuleId</a> - The SIP
--   rule ID.
newSipRule :: SipRule

-- | Indicates whether the SIP rule is enabled or disabled. You must
--   disable a rule before you can delete it.
sipRule_disabled :: Lens' SipRule (Maybe Bool)

-- | Target SIP media application and other details, such as priority and
--   AWS Region, to be specified in the SIP rule. Only one SIP rule per AWS
--   Region can be provided.
sipRule_targetApplications :: Lens' SipRule (Maybe (NonEmpty SipRuleTargetApplication))

-- | The type of trigger assigned to the SIP rule in <tt>TriggerValue</tt>,
--   currently <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt> or <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>.
sipRule_triggerType :: Lens' SipRule (Maybe SipRuleTriggerType)

-- | The time at which the SIP rule was last updated, in ISO 8601 format.
sipRule_updatedTimestamp :: Lens' SipRule (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The name of the SIP rule.
sipRule_name :: Lens' SipRule (Maybe Text)

-- | If <tt>TriggerType</tt> is <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt>, then the value
--   can be the outbound host name of the Amazon Chime Voice Connector. If
--   <tt>TriggerType</tt> is <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>, then the value can be
--   a customer-owned phone number in E164 format. <tt>SipRule</tt> is
--   triggered when a SIP rule requests host name or <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>
--   matches in the incoming SIP request.
sipRule_triggerValue :: Lens' SipRule (Maybe Text)

-- | The time at which the SIP rule was created, in ISO 8601 format.
sipRule_createdTimestamp :: Lens' SipRule (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The SIP rule ID.
sipRule_sipRuleId :: Lens' SipRule (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.Chime.Types.SipRule.SipRule
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Chime.Types.SipRule.SipRule
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.Chime.Types.SipRule.SipRule
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.Chime.Types.SipRule.SipRule
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.Chime.Types.SipRule.SipRule
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.Chime.Types.SipRule.SipRule
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.Chime.Types.SipRule.SipRule

module Network.AWS.Chime.Types.StreamingConfiguration

-- | The streaming configuration associated with an Amazon Chime Voice
--   Connector. Specifies whether media streaming is enabled for sending to
--   Amazon Kinesis, and shows the retention period for the Amazon Kinesis
--   data, in hours.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newStreamingConfiguration</a> smart constructor.
data StreamingConfiguration
StreamingConfiguration' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe (NonEmpty StreamingNotificationTarget) -> Natural -> StreamingConfiguration

-- | When true, media streaming to Amazon Kinesis is turned off.
[$sel:disabled:StreamingConfiguration'] :: StreamingConfiguration -> Maybe Bool

-- | The streaming notification targets.
[$sel:streamingNotificationTargets:StreamingConfiguration'] :: StreamingConfiguration -> Maybe (NonEmpty StreamingNotificationTarget)

-- | The retention period, in hours, for the Amazon Kinesis data.
[$sel:dataRetentionInHours:StreamingConfiguration'] :: StreamingConfiguration -> Natural

-- | Create a value of <a>StreamingConfiguration</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:disabled:StreamingConfiguration'</a>,
--   <a>streamingConfiguration_disabled</a> - When true, media streaming to
--   Amazon Kinesis is turned off.
--   
--   <a>$sel:streamingNotificationTargets:StreamingConfiguration'</a>,
--   <a>streamingConfiguration_streamingNotificationTargets</a> - The
--   streaming notification targets.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataRetentionInHours:StreamingConfiguration'</a>,
--   <a>streamingConfiguration_dataRetentionInHours</a> - The retention

module Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Termination

-- | Termination settings enable your SIP hosts to make outbound calls
--   using your Amazon Chime Voice Connector.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTermination</a> smart constructor.
data Termination
Termination' :: Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Natural -> Maybe [Text] -> Termination

-- | The default caller ID phone number.
[$sel:defaultPhoneNumber:Termination'] :: Termination -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | When termination settings are disabled, outbound calls can not be
--   made.
[$sel:disabled:Termination'] :: Termination -> Maybe Bool

-- | The countries to which calls are allowed, in ISO 3166-1 alpha-2
--   format. Required.
[$sel:callingRegions:Termination'] :: Termination -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The limit on calls per second. Max value based on account service
--   quota. Default value of 1.
[$sel:cpsLimit:Termination'] :: Termination -> Maybe Natural

-- | The IP addresses allowed to make calls, in CIDR format. Required.
[$sel:cidrAllowedList:Termination'] :: Termination -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Create a value of <a>Termination</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:defaultPhoneNumber:Termination'</a>,
--   <a>termination_defaultPhoneNumber</a> - The default caller ID phone
--   number.
--   
--   <a>$sel:disabled:Termination'</a>, <a>termination_disabled</a> - When
--   termination settings are disabled, outbound calls can not be made.
--   
--   <a>$sel:callingRegions:Termination'</a>,
--   <a>termination_callingRegions</a> - The countries to which calls are
--   allowed, in ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 format. Required.
--   
--   <a>$sel:cpsLimit:Termination'</a>, <a>termination_cpsLimit</a> - The
--   limit on calls per second. Max value based on account service quota.
--   Default value of 1.
--   
--   <a>$sel:cidrAllowedList:Termination'</a>,
--   <a>termination_cidrAllowedList</a> - The IP addresses allowed to make
--   calls, in CIDR format. Required.
newTermination :: Termination

-- | The default caller ID phone number.
termination_defaultPhoneNumber :: Lens' Termination (Maybe Text)

-- | When termination settings are disabled, outbound calls can not be
--   made.
termination_disabled :: Lens' Termination (Maybe Bool)

-- | The countries to which calls are allowed, in ISO 3166-1 alpha-2
--   format. Required.
termination_callingRegions :: Lens' Termination (Maybe [Text])

-- | The limit on calls per second. Max value based on account service
--   quota. Default value of 1.
termination_cpsLimit :: Lens' Termination (Maybe Natural)

-- | The IP addresses allowed to make calls, in CIDR format. Required.
termination_cidrAllowedList :: Lens' Termination (Maybe [Text])
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Termination.Termination
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Termination.Termination
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Termination.Termination
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Termination.Termination
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.Chime.Types.Termination.Termination

module Network.AWS.Chime.Types.EngineTranscribeMedicalSettings

-- | Settings specific to the Amazon Transcribe Medical engine.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEngineTranscribeMedicalSettings</a> smart
--   constructor.
data EngineTranscribeMedicalSettings

module Network.AWS.Chime.Types.User

-- | The user on the Amazon Chime account.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUser</a> smart constructor.
data User
User' :: Maybe InviteStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe License -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe RegistrationStatus -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe UserType -> Maybe AlexaForBusinessMetadata -> Text -> User

-- | The user invite status.
[$sel:userInvitationStatus:User'] :: User -> Maybe InviteStatus

-- | The user's personal meeting PIN.
[$sel:personalPIN:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | The primary phone number associated with the user.
[$sel:primaryProvisionedNumber:User'] :: User -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The license type for the user.
[$sel:licenseType:User'] :: User -> Maybe License

-- | Date and time when the user is registered, in ISO 8601 format.
[$sel:registeredOn:User'] :: User -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The Amazon Chime account ID.
[$sel:accountId:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | The user registration status.
[$sel:userRegistrationStatus:User'] :: User -> Maybe RegistrationStatus

-- | Date and time when the user is invited to the Amazon Chime account, in
--   ISO 8601 format.
[$sel:invitedOn:User'] :: User -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The display name of the user.
[$sel:displayName:User'] :: User -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The primary email address of the user.
[$sel:primaryEmail:User'] :: User -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The user type.
[$sel:userType:User'] :: User -> Maybe UserType

-- | The Alexa for Business metadata.
[$sel:alexaForBusinessMetadata:User'] :: User -> Maybe AlexaForBusinessMetadata

-- | The user ID.
[$sel:userId:User'] :: User -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>User</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:userInvitationStatus:User'</a>,
--   <a>user_userInvitationStatus</a> - The user invite status.
--   
--   <a>$sel:personalPIN:User'</a>, <a>user_personalPIN</a> - The user's
--   personal meeting PIN.
--   
--   <a>$sel:primaryProvisionedNumber:User'</a>,
--   <a>user_primaryProvisionedNumber</a> - The primary phone number
--   associated with the user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:licenseType:User'</a>, <a>user_licenseType</a> - The license
--   type for the user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:registeredOn:User'</a>, <a>user_registeredOn</a> - Date and
--   time when the user is registered, in ISO 8601 format.
--   
--   <a>$sel:accountId:User'</a>, <a>user_accountId</a> - The Amazon Chime
--   account ID.
--   
--   <a>$sel:userRegistrationStatus:User'</a>,
--   <a>user_userRegistrationStatus</a> - The user registration status.
--   
--   <a>$sel:invitedOn:User'</a>, <a>user_invitedOn</a> - Date and time
--   when the user is invited to the Amazon Chime account, in ISO 8601
--   format.
--   
--   <a>$sel:displayName:User'</a>, <a>user_displayName</a> - The display
--   name of the user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:primaryEmail:User'</a>, <a>user_primaryEmail</a> - The primary
--   email address of the user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:userType:User'</a>, <a>user_userType</a> - The user type.
--   
--   <a>$sel:alexaForBusinessMetadata:User'</a>,
--   <a>user_alexaForBusinessMetadata</a> - The Alexa for Business
--   metadata.
--   
--   <a>$sel:userId:User'</a>, <a>user_userId</a> - The user ID.
newUser :: Text -> User

-- | The user invite status.
user_userInvitationStatus :: Lens' User (Maybe InviteStatus)

-- | The user's personal meeting PIN.
user_personalPIN :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The primary phone number associated with the user.
user_primaryProvisionedNumber :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The license type for the user.
user_licenseType :: Lens' User (Maybe License)

-- | Date and time when the user is registered, in ISO 8601 format.
user_registeredOn :: Lens' User (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The Amazon Chime account ID.
user_accountId :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The user registration status.
user_userRegistrationStatus :: Lens' User (Maybe RegistrationStatus)

-- | Date and time when the user is invited to the Amazon Chime account, in
--   ISO 8601 format.
user_invitedOn :: Lens' User (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The display name of the user.
user_displayName :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The primary email address of the user.
user_primaryEmail :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The user type.
user_userType :: Lens' User (Maybe UserType)

-- | The Alexa for Business metadata.
user_alexaForBusinessMetadata :: Lens' User (Maybe AlexaForBusinessMetadata)

-- | The user ID.
user_userId :: Lens' User Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.Chime.Types.User.User
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.Chime.Types.User.User
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.Chime.Types.User.User
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.Chime.Types.User.User

--   host name and encryption settings.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newVoiceConnector</a> smart constructor.
data VoiceConnector

--   format.

--   Connector.

--   Default: <tt>us-east-1</tt>.

[$sel:voiceConnectorId:VoiceConnector'] :: VoiceConnector -> Maybe Text

-- | The ARN of the specified Amazon Chime Voice Connector.
[$sel:voiceConnectorArn:VoiceConnector'] :: VoiceConnector -> Maybe Text

--   format.

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   Voice Connector timestamp, in ISO 8601 format.
--   
--   <a>$sel:outboundHostName:VoiceConnector'</a>,
--   <a>voiceConnector_outboundHostName</a> - The outbound host name for
--   the Amazon Chime Voice Connector.

--   <a>$sel:name:VoiceConnector'</a>, <a>voiceConnector_name</a> - The
--   name of the Amazon Chime Voice Connector.
--

--   <a>voiceConnector_requireEncryption</a> - Designates whether

--

--   Default: <tt>us-east-1</tt>.

--   Amazon Chime Voice Connector.

module Network.AWS.Chime.Types.VoiceConnectorItem

--   Connectors to which to route inbound calls. Includes priority
--   configuration settings. Limit: 3 <tt>VoiceConnectorItems</tt> per
--   Amazon Chime Voice Connector group.

--   <i>See:</i> <a>newVoiceConnectorItem</a> smart constructor.

--   being the highest priority. Higher priority Amazon Chime Voice
--   Connectors are attempted first.

module Network.AWS.Chime.Types.VoiceConnectorGroup

-- | You don't have permissions to perform the requested operation.
_AccessDeniedException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The client exceeded its request rate limit.
_ThrottledClientException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The request exceeds the resource limit.
_ResourceLimitExceededException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The request was well-formed but was unable to be followed due to
--   semantic errors.
_UnprocessableEntityException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The request could not be processed because of conflict in the current
--   state of the resource.
_ConflictException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The client is permanently forbidden from making the request.
_ForbiddenException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | One or more of the resources in the request does not exist in the
--   system.
_NotFoundException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The service encountered an unexpected error.
_ServiceFailureException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The client is not currently authorized to make the request.
_UnauthorizedClientException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The service is currently unavailable.
_ServiceUnavailableException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The input parameters don't match the service's restrictions.
_BadRequestException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The Amazon Chime account details. An AWS account can have multiple
--   Amazon Chime accounts.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAccount</a> smart constructor.
data Account
Account' :: Maybe [SigninDelegateGroup] -> Maybe AccountStatus -> Maybe License -> Maybe [License] -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe AccountType -> Text -> Text -> Text -> Account

-- | The sign-in delegate groups associated with the account.
[$sel:signinDelegateGroups:Account'] :: Account -> Maybe [SigninDelegateGroup]

-- | The status of the account.
[$sel:accountStatus:Account'] :: Account -> Maybe AccountStatus

-- | The default license for the Amazon Chime account.
[$sel:defaultLicense:Account'] :: Account -> Maybe License

-- | Supported licenses for the Amazon Chime account.
[$sel:supportedLicenses:Account'] :: Account -> Maybe [License]

-- | The Amazon Chime account creation timestamp, in ISO 8601 format.
[$sel:createdTimestamp:Account'] :: Account -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The Amazon Chime account type. For more information about different
--   account types, see <a>Managing Your Amazon Chime Accounts</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon Chime Administration Guide</i>.
[$sel:accountType:Account'] :: Account -> Maybe AccountType

-- | The AWS account ID.
[$sel:awsAccountId:Account'] :: Account -> Text

-- | The Amazon Chime account ID.
[$sel:accountId:Account'] :: Account -> Text

-- | The Amazon Chime account name.
[$sel:name:Account'] :: Account -> Text

-- | An Amazon Chime SDK meeting attendee. Includes a unique
--   <tt>AttendeeId</tt> and <tt>JoinToken</tt> . The <tt>JoinToken</tt>
--   allows a client to authenticate and join as the specified attendee.
--   The <tt>JoinToken</tt> expires when the meeting ends or when
--   DeleteAttendee is called. After that, the attendee is unable to join
--   the meeting.
--   
--   We recommend securely transferring each <tt>JoinToken</tt> from your
--   server application to the client so that no other client has access to
--   the token except for the one authorized to represent the attendee.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAttendee</a> smart constructor.
data Attendee
Attendee' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Attendee

-- | The Amazon Chime SDK attendee ID.
[$sel:attendeeId:Attendee'] :: Attendee -> Maybe Text

-- | The join token used by the Amazon Chime SDK attendee.
[$sel:joinToken:Attendee'] :: Attendee -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The Amazon Chime SDK external user ID. An idempotency token. Links the
--   attendee to an identity managed by a builder application.
[$sel:externalUserId:Attendee'] :: Attendee -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | Create a value of <a>Attendee</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:attendeeId:Attendee'</a>, <a>attendee_attendeeId</a> - The
--   Amazon Chime SDK attendee ID.
--   
--   <a>$sel:joinToken:Attendee'</a>, <a>attendee_joinToken</a> - The join
--   token used by the Amazon Chime SDK attendee.
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalUserId:Attendee'</a>, <a>attendee_externalUserId</a> -
--   The Amazon Chime SDK external user ID. An idempotency token. Links the

-- | Origination routes define call distribution properties for your SIP
--   hosts to receive inbound calls using your Amazon Chime Voice
--   Connector. Limit: Ten origination routes for each Amazon Chime Voice
--   Connector.
--   
--   The parameters listed below are not required, but you must use at
--   least one.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOriginationRoute</a> smart constructor.
data OriginationRoute
OriginationRoute' :: Maybe Natural -> Maybe Natural -> Maybe OriginationRouteProtocol -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Natural -> OriginationRoute

-- | The priority associated with the host, with 1 being the highest
--   priority. Higher priority hosts are attempted first.
[$sel:priority:OriginationRoute'] :: OriginationRoute -> Maybe Natural

-- | The weight associated with the host. If hosts are equal in priority,
--   calls are redistributed among them based on their relative weight.
[$sel:weight:OriginationRoute'] :: OriginationRoute -> Maybe Natural

-- | The protocol to use for the origination route. Encryption-enabled
--   Amazon Chime Voice Connectors use TCP protocol by default.
[$sel:protocol:OriginationRoute'] :: OriginationRoute -> Maybe OriginationRouteProtocol

-- | The FQDN or IP address to contact for origination traffic.
[$sel:host:OriginationRoute'] :: OriginationRoute -> Maybe Text

-- | The designated origination route port. Defaults to 5060.
[$sel:port:OriginationRoute'] :: OriginationRoute -> Maybe Natural

-- | Create a value of <a>OriginationRoute</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.

--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding

--   host, with 1 being the highest priority. Higher priority hosts are
--   attempted first.
--   
--   <a>$sel:weight:OriginationRoute'</a>, <a>originationRoute_weight</a> -
--   The weight associated with the host. If hosts are equal in priority,
--   calls are redistributed among them based on their relative weight.
--   
--   <a>$sel:protocol:OriginationRoute'</a>,
--   <a>originationRoute_protocol</a> - The protocol to use for the
--   origination route. Encryption-enabled Amazon Chime Voice Connectors
--   use TCP protocol by default.
--   
--   <a>$sel:host:OriginationRoute'</a>, <a>originationRoute_host</a> - The
--   FQDN or IP address to contact for origination traffic.
--   
--   <a>$sel:port:OriginationRoute'</a>, <a>originationRoute_port</a> - The
--   designated origination route port. Defaults to 5060.

--   phone number with that of the first participant.

-- | The SIP rule details, including name, triggers, and target
--   applications. An AWS account can have multiple SIP rules.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSipRule</a> smart constructor.
data SipRule
SipRule' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe (NonEmpty SipRuleTargetApplication) -> Maybe SipRuleTriggerType -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> SipRule

-- | Indicates whether the SIP rule is enabled or disabled. You must
--   disable a rule before you can delete it.
[$sel:disabled:SipRule'] :: SipRule -> Maybe Bool

-- | Target SIP media application and other details, such as priority and
--   AWS Region, to be specified in the SIP rule. Only one SIP rule per AWS
--   Region can be provided.
[$sel:targetApplications:SipRule'] :: SipRule -> Maybe (NonEmpty SipRuleTargetApplication)

-- | The type of trigger assigned to the SIP rule in <tt>TriggerValue</tt>,
--   currently <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt> or <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>.
[$sel:triggerType:SipRule'] :: SipRule -> Maybe SipRuleTriggerType

-- | The time at which the SIP rule was last updated, in ISO 8601 format.
[$sel:updatedTimestamp:SipRule'] :: SipRule -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The name of the SIP rule.
[$sel:name:SipRule'] :: SipRule -> Maybe Text

-- | If <tt>TriggerType</tt> is <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt>, then the value
--   can be the outbound host name of the Amazon Chime Voice Connector. If
--   <tt>TriggerType</tt> is <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>, then the value can be
--   a customer-owned phone number in E164 format. <tt>SipRule</tt> is
--   triggered when a SIP rule requests host name or <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>
--   matches in the incoming SIP request.
[$sel:triggerValue:SipRule'] :: SipRule -> Maybe Text

-- | The time at which the SIP rule was created, in ISO 8601 format.
[$sel:createdTimestamp:SipRule'] :: SipRule -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The SIP rule ID.
[$sel:sipRuleId:SipRule'] :: SipRule -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>SipRule</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:disabled:SipRule'</a>, <a>sipRule_disabled</a> - Indicates

-- | Termination settings enable your SIP hosts to make outbound calls
--   using your Amazon Chime Voice Connector.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTermination</a> smart constructor.
data Termination

-- | The default caller ID phone number.
[$sel:defaultPhoneNumber:Termination'] :: Termination -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | When termination settings are disabled, outbound calls can not be
--   made.
[$sel:disabled:Termination'] :: Termination -> Maybe Bool

-- | The countries to which calls are allowed, in ISO 3166-1 alpha-2
--   format. Required.
[$sel:callingRegions:Termination'] :: Termination -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The limit on calls per second. Max value based on account service
--   quota. Default value of 1.
[$sel:cpsLimit:Termination'] :: Termination -> Maybe Natural

-- | The IP addresses allowed to make calls, in CIDR format. Required.
[$sel:cidrAllowedList:Termination'] :: Termination -> Maybe [Text]

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   number.
--

--   termination settings are disabled, outbound calls can not be made.
--   
--   <a>$sel:callingRegions:Termination'</a>,

--   allowed, in ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 format. Required.

-- | Sends a message to a particular channel that the member is a part of.
--   
--   The <tt>x-amz-chime-bearer</tt> request header is mandatory. Use the
--   <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call as the
--   value in the header.
--   
--   Also, <tt>STANDARD</tt> messages can contain 4KB of data and the 1KB
--   of metadata. <tt>CONTROL</tt> messages can contain 30 bytes of data
--   and no metadata.
module Network.AWS.Chime.SendChannelMessage

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newSendChannelMessage</a> smart constructor.
data SendChannelMessage
SendChannelMessage' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Text -> Sensitive Text -> ChannelMessageType -> ChannelMessagePersistenceType -> Sensitive Text -> SendChannelMessage

-- | The <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call.
[$sel:chimeBearer:SendChannelMessage'] :: SendChannelMessage -> Maybe Text

-- | The optional metadata for each message.
[$sel:metadata:SendChannelMessage'] :: SendChannelMessage -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The ARN of the channel.
[$sel:channelArn:SendChannelMessage'] :: SendChannelMessage -> Text

-- | The content of the message.
[$sel:content:SendChannelMessage'] :: SendChannelMessage -> Sensitive Text

-- | The type of message, <tt>STANDARD</tt> or <tt>CONTROL</tt>.
[$sel:type':SendChannelMessage'] :: SendChannelMessage -> ChannelMessageType

-- | Boolean that controls whether the message is persisted on the back
--   end. Required.
[$sel:persistence:SendChannelMessage'] :: SendChannelMessage -> ChannelMessagePersistenceType

-- | The <tt>Idempotency</tt> token for each client request.
[$sel:clientRequestToken:SendChannelMessage'] :: SendChannelMessage -> Sensitive Text

-- | Create a value of <a>SendChannelMessage</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:chimeBearer:SendChannelMessage'</a>,
--   <a>sendChannelMessage_chimeBearer</a> - The
--   <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call.
--   
--   <a>$sel:metadata:SendChannelMessage'</a>,
--   <a>sendChannelMessage_metadata</a> - The optional metadata for each
--   message.
--   
--   <a>$sel:channelArn:SendChannelMessage'</a>,
--   <a>sendChannelMessage_channelArn</a> - The ARN of the channel.
--   
--   <a>$sel:content:SendChannelMessage'</a>,
--   <a>sendChannelMessage_content</a> - The content of the message.
--   
--   <a>$sel:type':SendChannelMessage'</a>, <a>sendChannelMessage_type</a>
--   - The type of message, <tt>STANDARD</tt> or <tt>CONTROL</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:persistence:SendChannelMessage'</a>,
--   <a>sendChannelMessage_persistence</a> - Boolean that controls whether
--   the message is persisted on the back end. Required.
--   
--   <a>$sel:clientRequestToken:SendChannelMessage'</a>,
--   <a>sendChannelMessage_clientRequestToken</a> - The
--   <tt>Idempotency</tt> token for each client request.
newSendChannelMessage :: Text -> Text -> ChannelMessageType -> ChannelMessagePersistenceType -> Text -> SendChannelMessage

-- | The <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call.
sendChannelMessage_chimeBearer :: Lens' SendChannelMessage (Maybe Text)

-- | The optional metadata for each message.
sendChannelMessage_metadata :: Lens' SendChannelMessage (Maybe Text)

-- | The ARN of the channel.
sendChannelMessage_channelArn :: Lens' SendChannelMessage Text

-- | The content of the message.
sendChannelMessage_content :: Lens' SendChannelMessage Text

-- | The type of message, <tt>STANDARD</tt> or <tt>CONTROL</tt>.
sendChannelMessage_type :: Lens' SendChannelMessage ChannelMessageType

-- | Boolean that controls whether the message is persisted on the back
--   end. Required.
sendChannelMessage_persistence :: Lens' SendChannelMessage ChannelMessagePersistenceType

-- | The <tt>Idempotency</tt> token for each client request.
sendChannelMessage_clientRequestToken :: Lens' SendChannelMessage Text

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newSendChannelMessageResponse</a> smart constructor.
data SendChannelMessageResponse
SendChannelMessageResponse' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Int -> SendChannelMessageResponse

-- | The ARN of the channel.
[$sel:channelArn:SendChannelMessageResponse'] :: SendChannelMessageResponse -> Maybe Text

-- | The ID string assigned to each message.
[$sel:messageId:SendChannelMessageResponse'] :: SendChannelMessageResponse -> Maybe Text

[$sel:httpStatus:SendChannelMessageResponse'] :: SendChannelMessageResponse -> Int

-- | Searches for phone numbers that can be ordered. For US numbers,
--   provide at least one of the following search filters:
--   <tt>AreaCode</tt>, <tt>City</tt>, <tt>State</tt>, or
--   <tt>TollFreePrefix</tt>. If you provide <tt>City</tt>, you must also
--   provide <tt>State</tt>. Numbers outside the US only support the
--   <tt>PhoneNumberType</tt> filter, which you must use.
module Network.AWS.Chime.SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newSearchAvailablePhoneNumbers</a> smart constructor.
data SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers
SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers' :: Maybe PhoneNumberType -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Natural -> SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers

-- | The phone number type used to filter results. Required for non-US
--   numbers.
[$sel:phoneNumberType:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'] :: SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers -> Maybe PhoneNumberType

-- | The state used to filter results. Required only if you provide
--   <tt>City</tt>. Only applies to the US.
[$sel:state:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'] :: SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers -> Maybe Text

-- | The toll-free prefix that you use to filter results. Only applies to
--   the US.
[$sel:tollFreePrefix:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'] :: SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers -> Maybe Text

-- | The country used to filter results. Defaults to the US Format: ISO
--   3166-1 alpha-2.
[$sel:country:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'] :: SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers -> Maybe Text

-- | The token used to retrieve the next page of results.
[$sel:nextToken:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'] :: SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers -> Maybe Text

-- | The city used to filter results. Only applies to the US.
[$sel:city:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'] :: SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers -> Maybe Text

-- | The area code used to filter results. Only applies to the US.
[$sel:areaCode:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'] :: SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers -> Maybe Text

-- | The maximum number of results to return in a single call.
[$sel:maxResults:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'] :: SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers -> Maybe Natural

-- | Create a value of <a>SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:phoneNumberType:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'</a>,
--   <a>searchAvailablePhoneNumbers_phoneNumberType</a> - The phone number
--   type used to filter results. Required for non-US numbers.
--   
--   <a>$sel:state:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'</a>,
--   <a>searchAvailablePhoneNumbers_state</a> - The state used to filter
--   results. Required only if you provide <tt>City</tt>. Only applies to
--   the US.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tollFreePrefix:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'</a>,
--   <a>searchAvailablePhoneNumbers_tollFreePrefix</a> - The toll-free
--   prefix that you use to filter results. Only applies to the US.
--   
--   <a>$sel:country:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'</a>,
--   <a>searchAvailablePhoneNumbers_country</a> - The country used to
--   filter results. Defaults to the US Format: ISO 3166-1 alpha-2.
--   
--   <a>$sel:nextToken:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'</a>,
--   <a>searchAvailablePhoneNumbers_nextToken</a> - The token used to
--   retrieve the next page of results.
--   
--   <a>$sel:city:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'</a>,
--   <a>searchAvailablePhoneNumbers_city</a> - The city used to filter
--   results. Only applies to the US.
--   
--   <a>$sel:areaCode:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'</a>,
--   <a>searchAvailablePhoneNumbers_areaCode</a> - The area code used to
--   filter results. Only applies to the US.
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxResults:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'</a>,
--   <a>searchAvailablePhoneNumbers_maxResults</a> - The maximum number of
--   results to return in a single call.
newSearchAvailablePhoneNumbers :: SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers

-- | The phone number type used to filter results. Required for non-US
--   numbers.
searchAvailablePhoneNumbers_phoneNumberType :: Lens' SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers (Maybe PhoneNumberType)

-- | The state used to filter results. Required only if you provide
--   <tt>City</tt>. Only applies to the US.
searchAvailablePhoneNumbers_state :: Lens' SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers (Maybe Text)

-- | The toll-free prefix that you use to filter results. Only applies to
--   the US.
searchAvailablePhoneNumbers_tollFreePrefix :: Lens' SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers (Maybe Text)

-- | The country used to filter results. Defaults to the US Format: ISO
--   3166-1 alpha-2.
searchAvailablePhoneNumbers_country :: Lens' SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers (Maybe Text)

-- | The token used to retrieve the next page of results.
searchAvailablePhoneNumbers_nextToken :: Lens' SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers (Maybe Text)

-- | The city used to filter results. Only applies to the US.
searchAvailablePhoneNumbers_city :: Lens' SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers (Maybe Text)

-- | The area code used to filter results. Only applies to the US.
searchAvailablePhoneNumbers_areaCode :: Lens' SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers (Maybe Text)

-- | The maximum number of results to return in a single call.
searchAvailablePhoneNumbers_maxResults :: Lens' SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers (Maybe Natural)

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newSearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse</a> smart
--   constructor.
data SearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse
SearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse' :: Maybe [Sensitive Text] -> Maybe Text -> Int -> SearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse

-- | List of phone numbers, in E.164 format.
[$sel:e164PhoneNumbers:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse'] :: SearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse -> Maybe [Sensitive Text]

-- | The token used to retrieve the next page of search results.
[$sel:nextToken:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse'] :: SearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse -> Maybe Text

-- | The response's http status code.
[$sel:httpStatus:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse'] :: SearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse -> Int

-- | Create a value of <a>SearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:e164PhoneNumbers:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse'</a>,
--   <a>searchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse_e164PhoneNumbers</a> - List of
--   phone numbers, in E.164 format.
--   
--   <a>$sel:nextToken:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbers'</a>,
--   <a>searchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse_nextToken</a> - The token used
--   to retrieve the next page of search results.
--   
--   <a>$sel:httpStatus:SearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse'</a>,
--   <a>searchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse_httpStatus</a> - The response's
--   http status code.
newSearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse :: Int -> SearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse

-- | List of phone numbers, in E.164 format.
searchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse_e164PhoneNumbers :: Lens' SearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse (Maybe [Text])

-- | The token used to retrieve the next page of search results.
searchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse_nextToken :: Lens' SearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse (Maybe Text)

-- | The response's http status code.
searchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse_httpStatus :: Lens' SearchAvailablePhoneNumbersResponse Int

-- | Redacts message content, but not metadata. The message exists in the
--   back end, but the action returns null content, and the state shows as
--   redacted.
--   
--   The <tt>x-amz-chime-bearer</tt> request header is mandatory. Use the
--   <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call as the
--   value in the header.
module Network.AWS.Chime.RedactChannelMessage

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newRedactChannelMessage</a> smart constructor.
data RedactChannelMessage
RedactChannelMessage' :: Maybe Text -> Text -> Text -> RedactChannelMessage

-- | The <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call.
[$sel:chimeBearer:RedactChannelMessage'] :: RedactChannelMessage -> Maybe Text

-- | The ARN of the channel containing the messages that you want to
--   redact.
[$sel:channelArn:RedactChannelMessage'] :: RedactChannelMessage -> Text

-- | The ID of the message being redacted.
[$sel:messageId:RedactChannelMessage'] :: RedactChannelMessage -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>RedactChannelMessage</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:chimeBearer:RedactChannelMessage'</a>,
--   <a>redactChannelMessage_chimeBearer</a> - The
--   <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call.
--   
--   <a>$sel:channelArn:RedactChannelMessage'</a>,
--   <a>redactChannelMessage_channelArn</a> - The ARN of the channel
--   containing the messages that you want to redact.
--   
--   <a>$sel:messageId:RedactChannelMessage'</a>,
--   <a>redactChannelMessage_messageId</a> - The ID of the message being
--   redacted.
newRedactChannelMessage :: Text -> Text -> RedactChannelMessage

-- | The <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call.
redactChannelMessage_chimeBearer :: Lens' RedactChannelMessage (Maybe Text)

-- | The ARN of the channel containing the messages that you want to
--   redact.
redactChannelMessage_channelArn :: Lens' RedactChannelMessage Text

-- | The ID of the message being redacted.
redactChannelMessage_messageId :: Lens' RedactChannelMessage Text

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newRedactChannelMessageResponse</a> smart constructor.
data RedactChannelMessageResponse
RedactChannelMessageResponse' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Int -> RedactChannelMessageResponse

-- | The ARN of the channel containing the messages that you want to

-- | Puts retention settings for the specified Amazon Chime Enterprise
--   account. We recommend using AWS CloudTrail to monitor usage of this
--   API for your account. For more information, see <a>Logging Amazon
--   Chime API Calls with AWS CloudTrail</a> in the <i>Amazon Chime
--   Administration Guide</i>.
--   
--   To turn off existing retention settings, remove the number of days
--   from the corresponding <b>RetentionDays</b> field in the
--   <b>RetentionSettings</b> object. For more information about retention
--   settings, see <a>Managing Chat Retention Policies</a> in the <i>Amazon

-- | Lists all Channels created under a single Chime App as a paginated
--   list. You can specify filters to narrow results.
--   
--   <b>Functionality &amp; restrictions</b>
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Use privacy = <tt>PUBLIC</tt> to retrieve all public channels in
--   the account.</li>
--   <li>Only an <tt>AppInstanceAdmin</tt> can set privacy =
--   <tt>PRIVATE</tt> to list the private channels in an account.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   The <tt>x-amz-chime-bearer</tt> request header is mandatory. Use the
--   <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call as the
--   value in the header.
module Network.AWS.Chime.ListChannels

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newListChannels</a> smart constructor.
data ListChannels
ListChannels' :: Maybe ChannelPrivacy -> Maybe Text -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe Natural -> Text -> ListChannels

-- | The privacy setting. <tt>PUBLIC</tt> retrieves all the public
--   channels. <tt>PRIVATE</tt> retrieves private channels. Only an
--   <tt>AppInstanceAdmin</tt> can retrieve private channels.
[$sel:privacy:ListChannels'] :: ListChannels -> Maybe ChannelPrivacy

-- | The <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call.
[$sel:chimeBearer:ListChannels'] :: ListChannels -> Maybe Text

-- | The token passed by previous API calls until all requested channels
--   are returned.
[$sel:nextToken:ListChannels'] :: ListChannels -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The maximum number of channels that you want to return.
[$sel:maxResults:ListChannels'] :: ListChannels -> Maybe Natural

-- | The ARN of the <tt>AppInstance</tt>.
[$sel:appInstanceArn:ListChannels'] :: ListChannels -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ListChannels</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   privacy setting. <tt>PUBLIC</tt> retrieves all the public channels.
--   <tt>PRIVATE</tt> retrieves private channels. Only an
--   <tt>AppInstanceAdmin</tt> can retrieve private channels.
--   
--   <a>$sel:chimeBearer:ListChannels'</a>, <a>listChannels_chimeBearer</a>
--   - The <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call.
--   
--   <a>$sel:nextToken:ListChannels'</a>, <a>listChannels_nextToken</a> -
--   The token passed by previous API calls until all requested channels
--   are returned.
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxResults:ListChannels'</a>, <a>listChannels_maxResults</a> -
--   The maximum number of channels that you want to return.
--   
--   <a>$sel:appInstanceArn:ListChannels'</a>,
--   <a>listChannels_appInstanceArn</a> - The ARN of the
--   <tt>AppInstance</tt>.

-- | List all the messages in a channel. Returns a paginated list of
--   <tt>ChannelMessages</tt>. By default, sorted by creation timestamp in
--   descending order.
--   
--   Redacted messages appear in the results as empty, since they are only
--   redacted, not deleted. Deleted messages do not appear in the results.
--   This action always returns the latest version of an edited message.
--   
--   Also, the x-amz-chime-bearer request header is mandatory. Use the
--   <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call as the
--   value in the header.
module Network.AWS.Chime.ListChannelMessages

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newListChannelMessages</a> smart constructor.
data ListChannelMessages
ListChannelMessages' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe SortOrder -> Maybe Natural -> Maybe POSIX -> Text -> ListChannelMessages

-- | The <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call.
[$sel:chimeBearer:ListChannelMessages'] :: ListChannelMessages -> Maybe Text

-- | The token passed by previous API calls until all requested messages
--   are returned.
[$sel:nextToken:ListChannelMessages'] :: ListChannelMessages -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The initial or starting time stamp for your requested messages.
[$sel:notBefore:ListChannelMessages'] :: ListChannelMessages -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The order in which you want messages sorted. Default is Descending,
--   based on time created.
[$sel:sortOrder:ListChannelMessages'] :: ListChannelMessages -> Maybe SortOrder

-- | The maximum number of messages that you want returned.
[$sel:maxResults:ListChannelMessages'] :: ListChannelMessages -> Maybe Natural

-- | The final or ending time stamp for your requested messages.
[$sel:notAfter:ListChannelMessages'] :: ListChannelMessages -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The ARN of the channel.
[$sel:channelArn:ListChannelMessages'] :: ListChannelMessages -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ListChannelMessages</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:chimeBearer:ListChannelMessages'</a>,
--   <a>listChannelMessages_chimeBearer</a> - The
--   <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call.

--   <a>$sel:nextToken:ListChannelMessages'</a>,
--   <a>listChannelMessages_nextToken</a> - The token passed by previous
--   API calls until all requested messages are returned.
--   
--   <a>$sel:notBefore:ListChannelMessages'</a>,
--   <a>listChannelMessages_notBefore</a> - The initial or starting time
--   stamp for your requested messages.

--   <a>listChannelMessages_channelArn</a> - The ARN of the channel.

-- | The <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call.
listChannelMessages_chimeBearer :: Lens' ListChannelMessages (Maybe Text)

-- | The token passed by previous API calls until all requested messages
--   are returned.
listChannelMessages_nextToken :: Lens' ListChannelMessages (Maybe Text)

-- | The initial or starting time stamp for your requested messages.
listChannelMessages_notBefore :: Lens' ListChannelMessages (Maybe UTCTime)

--   based on time created.

--   value in the header.
