--   You can filter accounts by account name prefix. To find out which
--   Amazon Chime account a user belongs to, you can filter by the user's
--   email address, which returns one account result.
--   
--   This operation returns paginated results.

-- | Deletes the specified Amazon Chime account. You must suspend all users
--   before deleting <tt>Team</tt> account. You can use the
--   BatchSuspendUser action to dodo.
--   
--   For <tt>EnterpriseLWA</tt> and <tt>EnterpriseAD</tt> accounts, you
--   must release the claimed domains for your Amazon Chime account before
--   deletion. As soon as you release the domain, all users under that
--   account are suspended.
--   
--   Deleted accounts appear in your <tt>Disabled</tt> accounts list for 90
--   days. To restore deleted account from your <tt>Disabled</tt> accounts
--   list, you must contact AWS Support.
--   
--   After 90 days, deleted accounts are permanently removed from your
--   <tt>Disabled</tt> accounts list.
module Network.AWS.Chime.DeleteAccount

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newDeleteAccount</a> smart constructor.
data DeleteAccount

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   The Amazon Chime account ID.

-- | Creates an Amazon Chime Voice Connector under the administrator's AWS
--   account. You can choose to create an Amazon Chime Voice Connector in a
--   specific AWS Region.
--   
--   Enabling CreateVoiceConnectorRequest$RequireEncryption configures your
--   Amazon Chime Voice Connector to use TLS transport for SIP signaling
--   and Secure RTP (SRTP) for media. Inbound calls use TLS transport, and
--   unencrypted outbound calls are blocked.

-- | Creates a SIP rule which can be used to run a SIP media application as
--   a target for a specific trigger type.
module Network.AWS.Chime.CreateSipRule

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newCreateSipRule</a> smart constructor.
data CreateSipRule
CreateSipRule' :: Maybe Bool -> Text -> SipRuleTriggerType -> Text -> NonEmpty SipRuleTargetApplication -> CreateSipRule

-- | Enables or disables a rule. You must disable rules before you can
--   delete them.
[$sel:disabled:CreateSipRule'] :: CreateSipRule -> Maybe Bool

-- | The name of the SIP rule.
[$sel:name:CreateSipRule'] :: CreateSipRule -> Text

-- | The type of trigger assigned to the SIP rule in <tt>TriggerValue</tt>,
--   currently <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt> or <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>.
[$sel:triggerType:CreateSipRule'] :: CreateSipRule -> SipRuleTriggerType

-- | If <tt>TriggerType</tt> is <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt>, the value can
--   be the outbound host name of an Amazon Chime Voice Connector. If
--   <tt>TriggerType</tt> is <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>, the value can be a
--   customer-owned phone number in the E164 format. The
--   <tt>SipMediaApplication</tt> specified in the <tt>SipRule</tt> is
--   triggered if the request URI in an incoming SIP request matches the
--   <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt>, or if the <tt>To</tt> header in the
--   incoming SIP request matches the <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt> value.
[$sel:triggerValue:CreateSipRule'] :: CreateSipRule -> Text

-- | List of SIP media applications with priority and AWS Region. Only one
--   SIP application per AWS Region can be used.
[$sel:targetApplications:CreateSipRule'] :: CreateSipRule -> NonEmpty SipRuleTargetApplication

-- | Create a value of <a>CreateSipRule</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   customer-owned phone number in the E164 format. The

-- | Creates a chat room for the specified Amazon Chime Enterprise account.
module Network.AWS.Chime.CreateRoom

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newCreateRoom</a> smart constructor.

-- | Uses the join token and call metadata in a meeting request (From
--   number, To number, and so forth) to initiate an outbound call to a
--   public switched telephone network (PSTN) and join them into a Chime
--   meeting. Also ensures that the From number belongs to the customer.
--   
--   To play welcome audio or implement an interactive voice response
--   (IVR), use the <tt>CreateSipMediaApplicationCall</tt> action with the
--   corresponding SIP media application ID.
module Network.AWS.Chime.CreateMeetingDialOut

-- | Creates a new <tt>ChannelModerator</tt>. A channel moderator can:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Add and remove other members of the channel.</li>
--   <li>Add and remove other moderators of the channel.</li>
--   <li>Add and remove user bans for the channel.</li>
--   <li>Redact messages in the channel.</li>
--   <li>List messages in the channel.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   The <tt>x-amz-chime-bearer</tt> request header is mandatory. Use the
--   <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call as the
--   value in the header.
module Network.AWS.Chime.CreateChannelModerator

-- | Adds a user to a channel. The <tt>InvitedBy</tt> response field is
--   derived from the request header. A channel member can:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>List messages</li>
--   <li>Send messages</li>
--   <li>Receive messages</li>
--   <li>Edit their own messages</li>
--   <li>Leave the channel</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Privacy settings impact this action as follows:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Public Channels: You do not need to be a member to list messages,
--   but you must be a member to send messages.</li>
--   <li>Private Channels: You must be a member to list or send
--   messages.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   The <tt>x-amz-chime-bearer</tt> request header is mandatory. Use the
--   <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call as the
--   value in the header.
module Network.AWS.Chime.CreateChannelMembership

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newCreateChannelMembership</a> smart constructor.
data CreateChannelMembership
CreateChannelMembership' :: Maybe Text -> Text -> Text -> ChannelMembershipType -> CreateChannelMembership

-- | The <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call.
[$sel:chimeBearer:CreateChannelMembership'] :: CreateChannelMembership -> Maybe Text

-- | The ARN of the channel to which you're adding users.
[$sel:channelArn:CreateChannelMembership'] :: CreateChannelMembership -> Text

-- | The ARN of the member you want to add to the channel.
[$sel:memberArn:CreateChannelMembership'] :: CreateChannelMembership -> Text

-- | The membership type of a user, <tt>DEFAULT</tt> or <tt>HIDDEN</tt>.
--   Default members are always returned as part of
--   <tt>ListChannelMemberships</tt>. Hidden members are only returned if
--   the type filter in <tt>ListChannelMemberships</tt> equals
--   <tt>HIDDEN</tt>. Otherwise hidden members are not returned. This is
--   only supported by moderators.
[$sel:type':CreateChannelMembership'] :: CreateChannelMembership -> ChannelMembershipType

-- | Create a value of <a>CreateChannelMembership</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.

-- | Permanently bans a member from a channel. Moderators can't add banned
--   members to a channel. To undo a ban, you first have to
--   <tt>DeleteChannelBan</tt>, and then <tt>CreateChannelMembership</tt>.
--   Bans are cleaned up when you delete users or channels.
--   
--   If you ban a user who is already part of a channel, that user is
--   automatically kicked from the channel.
--   
--   The <tt>x-amz-chime-bearer</tt> request header is mandatory. Use the
--   <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call as the
--   value in the header.
module Network.AWS.Chime.CreateChannelBan

--   banned.

-- | Creates a channel to which you can add users and send messages.
--   
--   <b>Restriction</b>: You can't change a channel's privacy.
--   
--   The <tt>x-amz-chime-bearer</tt> request header is mandatory. Use the
--   <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call as the
--   value in the header.

-- | The channel mode: <tt>UNRESTRICTED</tt> or <tt>RESTRICTED</tt>.
--   Administrators, moderators, and channel members can add themselves and
--   other members to unrestricted channels. Only administrators and
--   moderators can add members to restricted channels.
[$sel:mode:CreateChannel'] :: CreateChannel -> Maybe ChannelMode

-- | The channel's privacy level: <tt>PUBLIC</tt> or <tt>PRIVATE</tt>.
--   Private channels aren't discoverable by users outside the channel.
--   Public channels are discoverable by anyone in the
--   <tt>AppInstance</tt>.
[$sel:privacy:CreateChannel'] :: CreateChannel -> Maybe ChannelPrivacy

-- | The <tt>AppInstanceUserArn</tt> of the user that makes the API call.
[$sel:chimeBearer:CreateChannel'] :: CreateChannel -> Maybe Text

-- | The metadata of the creation request. Limited to 1KB and UTF-8.
[$sel:metadata:CreateChannel'] :: CreateChannel -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The tags for the creation request.
[$sel:tags:CreateChannel'] :: CreateChannel -> Maybe (NonEmpty Tag)

-- | The ARN of the channel request.
[$sel:appInstanceArn:CreateChannel'] :: CreateChannel -> Text

[$sel:name:CreateChannel'] :: CreateChannel -> Sensitive Text

[$sel:clientRequestToken:CreateChannel'] :: CreateChannel -> Sensitive Text

-- | Creates a new attendee for an active Amazon Chime SDK meeting. For
--   more information about the Amazon Chime SDK, see <a>Using the Amazon
--   Chime SDK</a> in the <i>Amazon Chime Developer Guide</i>.
module Network.AWS.Chime.CreateAttendee

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newCreateAttendee</a> smart constructor.
data CreateAttendee

-- | The Amazon Chime SDK external user ID. An idempotency token. Links the
--   attendee to an identity managed by a builder application.
[$sel:externalUserId:CreateAttendee'] :: CreateAttendee -> Sensitive Text

-- | Create a value of <a>CreateAttendee</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:tags:CreateAttendee'</a>, <a>createAttendee_tags</a> - The tag
--   key-value pairs.

--   <tt>AppInstance</tt>.</li>

-- | Updates phone number product types or calling names. You can update
--   one attribute at a time for each
--   <tt>UpdatePhoneNumberRequestItem</tt>. For example, you can update the
--   product type or the calling name.
--   
--   For toll-free numbers, you cannot use the Amazon Chime Business
--   Calling product type. For numbers outside the U.S., you must use the
--   Amazon Chime SIP Media Application Dial-In product type.
--   
--   Updates to outbound calling names can take up to 72 hours to complete.
--   Pending updates to outbound calling names must be complete before you
--   can request another update.

-- | Removes the suspension from up to 50 previously suspended users for
--   the specified Amazon Chime <tt>EnterpriseLWA</tt> account. Only users
--   on <tt>EnterpriseLWA</tt> accounts can be unsuspended using this
--   action. For more information about different account types, see
--   <a>Managing Your Amazon Chime Accounts</a> in the account types, in
--   the <i>Amazon Chime Administration Guide</i>.
--   
--   Previously suspended users who are unsuspended using this action are
--   returned to <tt>Registered</tt> status. Users who are not previously
--   suspended are ignored.

-- | Suspends up to 50 users from a <tt>Team</tt> or <tt>EnterpriseLWA</tt>
--   Amazon Chime account. For more information about different account
--   types, see <a>Managing Your Amazon Chime Accounts</a> in the <i>Amazon
--   Chime Administration Guide</i>.
--   
--   Users suspended from a <tt>Team</tt> account are disassociated from
--   the account,but they can continue to use Amazon Chime as free users.
--   To remove the suspension from suspended <tt>Team</tt> account users,
--   invite them to the <tt>Team</tt> account again. You can use the
--   InviteUsers action to do so.
--   
--   Users suspended from an <tt>EnterpriseLWA</tt> account are immediately
--   signed out of Amazon Chime and can no longer sign in. To remove the
--   suspension from suspended <tt>EnterpriseLWA</tt> account users, use
--   the BatchUnsuspendUser action.
--   
--   To sign out users without suspending them, use the LogoutUser action.
module Network.AWS.Chime.BatchSuspendUser

-- | Updates phone number details, such as product type or calling name,
--   for the specified phone number ID. You can update one phone number
--   detail at a time. For example, you can update either the product type
--   or the calling name in one action.
--   
--   For toll-free numbers, you cannot use the Amazon Chime Business
--   Calling product type. For numbers outside the U.S., you must use the
--   Amazon Chime SIP Media Application Dial-In product type.
--   
--   Updates to outbound calling names can take 72 hours to complete.
--   Pending updates to outbound calling names must be complete before you
--   can request another update.
module Network.AWS.Chime.UpdatePhoneNumber

-- | Enables or disables a rule. You must disable rules before you can

-- | The name of the SIP rule.
createSipRule_name :: Lens' CreateSipRule Text

-- | The type of trigger assigned to the SIP rule in <tt>TriggerValue</tt>,
--   currently <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt> or <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>.
createSipRule_triggerType :: Lens' CreateSipRule SipRuleTriggerType

-- | If <tt>TriggerType</tt> is <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt>, the value can
--   be the outbound host name of an Amazon Chime Voice Connector. If
--   <tt>TriggerType</tt> is <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>, the value can be a
--   customer-owned phone number in the E164 format. The
--   <tt>SipMediaApplication</tt> specified in the <tt>SipRule</tt> is
--   triggered if the request URI in an incoming SIP request matches the
--   <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt>, or if the <tt>To</tt> header in the
--   incoming SIP request matches the <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt> value.
createSipRule_triggerValue :: Lens' CreateSipRule Text

--   SIP application per AWS Region can be used.

--   target applications.

--   a signature for request authentication. The SDK clients authenticate
--   your requests by using access keys that you provide. For more

--   Line Interface User Guide</i>. For a list of available Amazon Chime

--   Command Reference</i>.</li>

--   supports signature version 4. For more information, see <a>Signature
--   Version 4 Signing Process</a> in the <i>Amazon Web Services General

--   <tt>SipRule</tt> is triggered if the request URI in an incoming SIP
--   request matches the <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt>, or if the <tt>To</tt>
--   header in the incoming SIP request matches the <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>
--   value.

-- | An Amazon Chime SDK meeting attendee. Includes a unique
--   <tt>AttendeeId</tt> and <tt>JoinToken</tt> . The <tt>JoinToken</tt>
--   allows a client to authenticate and join as the specified attendee.
--   The <tt>JoinToken</tt> expires when the meeting ends or when
--   DeleteAttendee is called. After that, the attendee is unable to join
--   the meeting.
--   
--   We recommend securely transferring each <tt>JoinToken</tt> from your
--   server application to the client so that no other client has access to
--   the token except for the one authorized to represent the attendee.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAttendee</a> smart constructor.
data Attendee
Attendee' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Attendee

-- | Create a value of <a>Attendee</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:attendeeId:Attendee'</a>, <a>attendee_attendeeId</a> - The
--   Amazon Chime SDK attendee ID.
--   
--   <a>$sel:joinToken:Attendee'</a>, <a>attendee_joinToken</a> - The join
--   token used by the Amazon Chime SDK attendee.
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalUserId:Attendee'</a>, <a>attendee_externalUserId</a> -
--   The Amazon Chime SDK external user ID. An idempotency token. Links the
--   attendee to an identity managed by a builder application.
newAttendee :: Attendee

--   host, with 1 being the highest priority. Higher priority hosts are
--   attempted first.
--   
--   <a>$sel:weight:OriginationRoute'</a>, <a>originationRoute_weight</a> -
--   The weight associated with the host. If hosts are equal in priority,
--   calls are redistributed among them based on their relative weight.

-- | The SIP rule details, including name, triggers, and target
--   applications. An AWS account can have multiple SIP rules.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSipRule</a> smart constructor.
data SipRule
SipRule' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe (NonEmpty SipRuleTargetApplication) -> Maybe SipRuleTriggerType -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> SipRule

-- | Create a value of <a>SipRule</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:disabled:SipRule'</a>, <a>sipRule_disabled</a> - Indicates
--   whether the SIP rule is enabled or disabled. You must disable a rule
--   before you can delete it.
--   
--   <a>$sel:targetApplications:SipRule'</a>,
--   <a>sipRule_targetApplications</a> - Target SIP media application and
--   other details, such as priority and AWS Region, to be specified in the
--   SIP rule. Only one SIP rule per AWS Region can be provided.
--   
--   <a>$sel:triggerType:SipRule'</a>, <a>sipRule_triggerType</a> - The
--   type of trigger assigned to the SIP rule in <tt>TriggerValue</tt>,
--   currently <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt> or <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:updatedTimestamp:SipRule'</a>, <a>sipRule_updatedTimestamp</a>
--   - The time at which the SIP rule was last updated, in ISO 8601 format.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:SipRule'</a>, <a>sipRule_name</a> - The name of the SIP
--   rule.
--   
--   <a>$sel:triggerValue:SipRule'</a>, <a>sipRule_triggerValue</a> - If
--   <tt>TriggerType</tt> is <tt>RequestUriHostname</tt>, then the value
--   can be the outbound host name of the Amazon Chime Voice Connector. If
--   <tt>TriggerType</tt> is <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>, then the value can be
--   a customer-owned phone number in E164 format. <tt>SipRule</tt> is
--   triggered when a SIP rule requests host name or <tt>ToPhoneNumber</tt>
--   matches in the incoming SIP request.

--   <a>$sel:createdTimestamp:SipRule'</a>, <a>sipRule_createdTimestamp</a>
